====================================
Installing ONIE on molex_ocs_16x16 (Intel(R) Atom(TM) CPU E3845) platform with UEFI
====================================

Prerequisites 
====================

1. molex ocs (Intel(R) Atom(TM) CPU E3845) platform
2. UEFI as primary bootloader
3. Grub2 as Coreboot payload
4. console connection with the same baud rate as your UEFI settings are


Cross-Compiling ONIE
====================

Because we are builing grub with coreboot support we have to install additional packages first prior of compiling ONIE.
All those packages are integrated into a script.
for ubuntu based system you can:

# sudo sh machine/molex/molex_ocs_16x16/build-env.sh

To compile ONIE change directories to ``build-config`` and then
type ``"make MACHINEROOT=../machine/molex MACHINE=molex_ocs_16x16 all"``.
For example::

  $ cd build-config
  $ make -j4 MACHINEROOT=../machine/molex MACHINE=molex_ocs_16x16 all

When complete, the ONIE binaries are located in
``build/images``::

-rw-rw-r-- 1 sonic sonic 28311552 Feb 20 00:48 onie-recovery-x86_64-molex_ocs_16x16-r0.iso
-rw-rw-r-- 1 sonic sonic 13365242 Feb 20 00:48 onie-updater-x86_64-molex_ocs_16x16-r0
-rw-rw-r-- 1 sonic sonic  7457380 Feb 20 00:47 molex_ocs_16x16-r0.initrd
-rw-rw-r-- 1 sonic sonic  5854880 Feb 20 00:48 molex_ocs_16x16-r0.vmlinuz


molex_ocs_16x16-r0.vmlinuz                  -- This is the ONIE kernel image

molex_ocs_16x16-r0.initrd                   -- This is the ONIE initramfs (filesystem)

onie-updater-x86_64-molex_ocs_16x16-r0      -- This is the ONIE self-update image.
                                        This image is a self-extracting archive used for installing ONIE.

onie-recovery-x86_64-molex_ocs_16x16-r0.iso -- This is iso image containing ONIE kernel + ONIE initramfs with ONIE self-update image already included inside.
                                        This might be very useful as it can be easily placed on USB/CD and one can boot from this to install/reinstall/repair ONIE
										   
Installation steps
====================

1. Put your onie-recovery-x86_64-molex_ocs_16x16-r0.iso onto USB
   # dd if=onie-recovery-x86_64-molex_ocs_16x16-r0.iso of=/dev/sdX bs=1M

2. Shutdown you platform and place you usb stick onto the platform

3. Boot to your coreboot's grub2

4. Press 'c' and type:
   grub> insmod ehci
   grub> search -n --set root -l ONIE-RECOVERY
   grub> echo $root
   
You should see something like:

  usb0,msdos1
  
Now load new grub configuration file:

  grub> configfile ($root)/boot/grub/grub.cfg
  
After that you should see:


                     GNU GRUB  version 2.02~beta2+e4a1fe391

